   "source": [
    "## About this notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook is the report for PokeTeam AI. It walks through the project\n",
    "end-to-end: the data I use, the embeddings I build from it, how I construct\n",
    "training labels, how the model is trained, and how recommendations are\n",
    "produced at inference time. Wherever there is something to look at (a chart,\n",
    "a sample team, a viability score), the code that produced it is right next to\n",
    "the explanation.\n",
    "\n",
    "### How to run it\n",
    "\n",
    "The notebook expects to live in the `notebooks/` directory of the project. It\n",
    "auto-detects the project root from there. To run from scratch on another\n",
    "machine:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. `pip install -r requirements.txt` from the project root\n",
    "2. `python tools/rebuild_chaos.py` to build the data artefacts (parquets,\n",
    "   embeddings, trained model). This takes a few minutes the first time.\n",
    "3. Open this notebook and run cells top to bottom.\n",
    "\n",
    "If any data artefact is missing, the corresponding cell will print a helpful\n",
    "message rather than crash, so you can run partial sections in isolation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
