    "## 7. Labelling the training data\n",
    "\n",
    "The LightGBM classifier is binary: each training example is either\n",
    "**label 1** (\"looks like a real high-rated team\") or **label 0** (\"doesn't\").\n",
    "The interesting design choice is how these examples are constructed, because\n",
    "that is where most of the model's signal-to-noise ratio is decided.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Positives (label 1) — Gibbs-sampled from chaos data\n",
    "\n",
    "A positive is a six-Pokemon team built by repeated sampling from the chaos\n",
    "teammate distributions: pick an anchor proportional to its usage, then each\n",
    "next member proportional to its co-occurrence weight with the team so far."
   ]
  },
