    "## 8. The trained model\n",
    "\n",
    "The classifier is LightGBM with around 200 trees and depth 5 — deliberately\n",
    "small. The reasoning is that the upstream beam search already encodes the\n",
    "strong signal (real co-occurrence data), so the model only needs to catch\n",
    "team-level problems (overlapping weaknesses, role imbalance) that the\n",
    "per-slot search cannot see.\n",
    "\n",
    "The trained model lives in `model/viability.lgb`."
   ]
